HEADWORD: Reptant
<hw>Rep"tant</hw> <pr>(r?p"t<it>a</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>reptans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>reptare</ets>, v.
intens. from <ets>repere</ets> to creep. See
<er>Reptile</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Same as <er>Repent</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Creeping; crawling; -- said of
reptiles, worms, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reptantia</ent>⟦br⟧
